
:INFO
Three Techniques, Endless Forms
Hand building uses three core methods: pinch, coil, and slab. \
Pinch pots are the fastest to learn and teach you the most about clay thickness. \
Coil building lets you make tall forms without a wheel. \
Slab construction is ideal for geometric shapes, mugs, and tiles. \
Most experienced potters combine all three in a single piece.

:PATH
